# ============================================================
# EXAMPLE RESPONSE — Error (invalid file / server error)
# ============================================================
#
# HTTP/1.1 500 Internal Server Error
#
# {
#   "status": "error",
#   "message": "Error description here"
# }


# ============================================================
# INTEGRATION QUICK REFERENCE
# ============================================================
#
# PRIMARY field   → ensemble_score (0–100)
#
# Risk thresholds:
#   0  – 30   LOW     → Genuine / passes cleanly
#   31 – 60   MEDIUM  → Suspicious, flag for manual review
#   61 – 100  HIGH    → Strong AI / synthetic indicators
#
# Per-model verdict:
#   Each model independently returns "AI Generated" or "Genuine"
#   based on its own score >= 50 threshold.
#
# Ensemble weights (when all 3 models available):
#   AASIST3   20%  — graph attention, spectro-temporal features
#   wav2vec2  45%  — transformer, self-supervised speech features
#   RawNet2   35%  — raw waveform CNN+GRU
#
# model_confidence:
#   1.0  → all models agree completely
#   0.0  → models disagree completely
#   Use this to decide whether to trust the result or flag for review.
#
# Segment scores:
#   Audio > 4s is split into overlapping 4s windows.
#   segment_scores contains per-window probabilities.
#   Useful for detecting partial spoofing in long recordings.
